®IN GRATEFUL AND LOVING MEMORY OF
COLONEL A. H. BRIDGES C.B. C.I.E. D.S.O. INDIAN ARMY
WHO LIVED ON THIS HILL FOR OVER 30 YEARS
THIS SEAT WAS ERECTED BY HIS FAMILY AND FRIENDS"¶
іGIVEN IN LOVING MEMORY OF
TOM HILLIER
A DEVOTED HUSBAND AND
FOR MANY YEARS A CHORISTER AND
PAROCHIAL CHURCH COUNCILLOR OF
St. MARY'S CHURCH, BATHWICK
DIED 18th.FEBRUARY 1969"№
¶Harold Swindells 
Co-founder of Bath Postal Museum
He enjoyed walking in this park 
and liked to stop and look at every tree. 
This Always made him smile 
because he loved trees"Ц
УNETFLIX
After Life
2019 -
This bench is donated by Netflix to commemorate Ricky Gervais' 'After Life'.

Life can be tough, but there's always hope.
Campaign Against Living Miserably (CALM) is on your side."Ц
УThis bench was donated for 
David Llewllyn Thomas. 
An old Edwardian who was born and lived at 
no.1 Royal Cresent. He particularly enjoyed 
sitting in this park in the summer listening 
to the band playing"Ь
ЩDedicated to the memory of
John Dennis Harper
07.11.1934 - 17.05.2013
Those we love don't go away, they walk beside us every day,
Unseen, unheard but still always near,
Still loved, still missed and with us here."Ь
